create 2 nodes and enable opasswordless authemntication 
then add the public ipv to inventory.ini file. 
i created my inventory.ini fole in Day-03 and inside 03-first-playbook.
i have creates my 'test' role also onside this
use ansible-galaxy role install<name> . example: 'ansible-galaxy role install bsmeding.docker'
to check where the role is installed. type 'ls ~/.ansible/roles'. this is inside home directory inside hidden ansible folder and inside that u have roles.
In cd 03-first-playbook. here we have our inventory.ini file . in this create 'vim docker-playbook.yaml'
---
- hosts: all
- become: true
- roles:
    - bsmeding.docker
in above yaml file we are mentioning the role that we installed from ansible galaxy
then type 'ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini docker-playbook.yaml'
docker will be installed on our 2 ec2 instance nodes. connect top instances and check for docker is installed or not
